{
  "text": "activation by transient overexpression suppressed the pro duction of these mRNAs. We cotransfected HEK293T cells with Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 plasmids, along with WT or an inactive mutant IRE1\ue061. Expression of Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 mRNAs was markedly suppressed by the cotransfected WT, but not mutant IRE1\ue061 (Fig. 8 A) . Similarly, cotransfected IRE1\ue061 reduced expression of Bloc1s1 mRNA, which has been identified as an IRE1\ue061 substrate for degradation in pre vious studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ).",
